deck: Forge of Creation is a place where the celestialsapiens are born. A chrono-randomization barrier surrounds the place, desynchronizing the place with time and space, making it impossible to get. Only celestialsapiens and Paradox can reach the Forge of Creation. However, Paradox is forbidden from coming any closer than 500 light years of it. The only other means of reaching the Forge is with the aid of the Map of Infinity. The forge is home to Mother Celestialsapien and Baby Celestialsapiens.
description:
Forge of Creation is the birthplace of Celestialsapiens and home of Mother Celestialsapiens. It is arguably the most important place in the known Ben 10 multiverse, a place that creates Omnipotent beings such as Ben 10's Alien X, with the power to recreate the entire universe after destroying it.

A pregnant Celestialsapien has a small glowing white orb in her hands with a baby Celestialsapien growing inside it. According to Dwayne, it takes a baby Celestialsapien tens of thousands of years to develop. Celestialsapiens are immensely powerful beings with the power to control reality. This ability is so powerful, merely thinking something makes it a reality. However, a Celestialsapien cannot do anything unless a majority or all of its personalities agree on it. They have spent eons debating before using any of their powers.

A baby Celestialsapien does not have multiple personalities, but it is also not mature enough to use its power. Aggregor tried to take advantage of this by absorbing a baby Celestialsapiens power to become a mighty god. Not riddled with dual personilities, Aggregor would have become impossible to be defeated by a mere mortal, and as with the powers of a Celestialsapien, he would have been immune to the effect of any manner of reality bending of any magnitude.

Each Celestialsapien has 2 distinct personalities inside them. There needs to be a 3rd agreeing for them to do anything. So while they are arguably the strongest beings in the multiverse, they are handicapped. Even when Forge of Creation was invaded by Aggregor to feed on the energy of a newborn Celestialsapien, the Mother Celestielsapien spent the entire time deliberating on what to do in the pocket dimension where her two personalities exist.

As the Forge is surrounded by a chrono-randomization barrier, it is impossible to get. Only the Celestialsapiens and Paradox can reach the Forge. Although, anyone using the Map of Infinity can do the same. Paradox himself is not allowed to come within 500 light years of the place. Alien X's split personalities Bellicus and Serena almost destroyed Paradox (by coming into an agreement), when he appeared in the dimension, before he managed to change Ben back to his human form.

Ali
name: Forge of Creation

deck: Eden Prime is a near-utopian planet in the Exodus Cluster, notable for being the first human-colonized world outside of the Sol system and thus a symbol for humanity's growing power and aspirations. However, it is most famous for being the target of a deadly geth attack in 2183.
description:
Eden Prime was the first human colony beyond the Charon mass relay, established by the Systems Alliance. Possessing a biosphere capable of supporting Earth-based plant life to an unprecedented extent, it quickly became a major agrarian center, providing food and fuel to the galaxy. The planet's success story became a symbol for humanity's ability to endure and thrive among the galactic community despite being the newcomers.

The tranquility of this world was threatened in 2183 when a geth attack force, led by the rogue Spectre Saren Arterius, attacked the planet and killed many colonists in their search for a newly discovered Prothean beacon.
name: Eden Prime

deck: Wonderworld was formerly a planet called Mammord that traversed the entirety of space-time. Later it became the center of metaphysical reality.
description:
Mammord was an ancient planet that traverses the entire space-time frontier at hyper-temporal speeds. During the primal times, the gods created the Theocracy and their leader Adam-One with the task of taming the world. For billions of years, Adam-One struggled against the chaos of his environment that was turned into Wonderworld. They created a planet spanning city called Omnitropolis and a Museum District that served as a site to store relics. From this site, the Theocracy defended the boundaries of the known universe. This included superbeings from ten thousand worlds where they helped defeat foes such as the A-Mind, a 5th Dimensional Imp and the infant universe Qwewq. It was devastated upon the escape of the anti-sun Mageddon weapon that killed the majority of the Theocracy.

The rests of Wonderworld still orbits the limit of reality, as their mysterious counterpart.

deck: Settlement in Texas and formerly home to Marvel's Western gunslingers in the 1800s. For a time it was ruled by the time-travelling Kang the Conqueror.
description:
Residents of Tombstone included Kid Colt, Phantom Rider, Rawhide Kid and Two-Gun Kid. Black Rider, Kid Cassidy and Reno Jones possibly also lived there. Kang the Conqueror ruled Tombstone making it his home for a time.

Visitors to Tombstone include various teams of Avengers during time travel adventures. The first team which visited Tombstone consisted of Hawkeye, Moondragon and Thor. This team visited during Kang's rule and allied with the western heroes to overthrow Kang which resulted in Two-Gun Kid joining the Avengers as an official member and journeying to present day time along with them.

A second team of Avengers consisting of Hawkeye, Iron Man, Mockingbird, Tigra and Wonder Man visited Tombstone some time after Kang's rule where they met Two-Gun Kid (who had since returned to his time) and his fellow gun-slingers. Although most of the team didn't remain there for long, Mockingbird was stranded in the time period when she was kidnapped by the Phantom Rider. Drugging her into compliance, Phantom Rider made Mockingbird into his "wife" and was hunted by the only available Avenger to save Mockingbird: Two-Gun Kid. Eventually shrugging off the effects of Phantom Rider's drugs, Mockingbird freed herself and fought the man who had abused her and watched happily as he fell of a cliff. The rest of the Avengers, now joined by Firebird, Hank Pym and Moon Knight, returned to bring Mockingbird back to the present day.

A third team of Avengers consisting of Hawkeye, Songbird and Yellowjacket also visited Tombstone, again during Kang's rule. Despite their desire to intervene and stop Kang, they were forced to avoid confronting Kang or helping as they knew Kang's rule would eventually be stopped by an early iteration of the Avengers sometime later. The team fought against Phantoms disguised as Black Rider, Kid Cassidy and Reno Jones.
